The paper discusses the challenges of implementing Visible Light Communication (VLC) in wearable computing, which involves networking computing devices. This topic falls under the category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper discusses the diversity found in current wearable devices, which suggests a focus on Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses the efficiency and energy costs of VLC compared to radio-frequency (RF) devices, which suggests a focus on Information Theory (cs.IT) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper mentions the drastic changes in light conditions due to mobility, which suggests a focus on Multimedia (cs.MM).
